programme.title: Live PGA Tour Golf
programme.desc: The CJ Cup. Coverage of day one of the second staging of the tournament, held at the Club at Nine Bridges on Jeju Island in South Korea. Justin Thomas prevailed at the inaugural staging of the event last year, beating Marc Leishman in a play-off after the two finished level on an overall score of nine-under par. While the American is not expected to be in attendance this year, the field will include a number of star names such as Paul Casey, Jason Day, Tony Finau, Tyrrel Hatton and Brooks Koepka.(c)

programme.desc: Arizona Cardinals v Denver Broncos (Kick-off 1.20am). Coverage of the match between the respective NFC West and AFC West sides, which takes place at State Farm Stadium in Phoenix. This is the opening fixture in week seven, and even at this early juncture a victory could do little to improve the hosts chances of reaching the play-offs this season, after they began the campaign with a number of consecutive losses. One ray of hope for Cardinals fans has been the introduction of rookie quarterback Josh Rosen, who was drafted from UCLA Bruins in the off-season, and appears to be a bright prospect for the future, who could inspire them to a reversal of fortunes.

programme.title: EFL Highlights
programme.sub-title: EFL Championship Play-Off Finals: Crystal Palace v Watford: 2012/13
programme.desc: Crystal Palace v Watford. Action from the 2012/13 Championship play-off final at Wembley Stadium, as the teams contested a place in the top flight alongside the already promoted Cardiff City and Hull City. Palace reached this match when Wilfried Zaha scored a brace in a 2-0 away win against Brighton & Hove Albion after a goalless draw in the first leg. Meanwhile, Watford bounced back from narrowly missing out on automatic promotion by overcoming Leicester City in dramatic fashion, with Troy Deeney scoring an injury time-winner on the counter after Manuel Almunia had saved a penalty.
